  "prompt": "What are the best TED Talks by youth?",
  "response": "Here are some notable TED Talks by young speakers:\n\n1. Malala Yousafzai - \"One child, one teacher, one book, and one pen can change the world\"\n- Delivered when she was 17\n- Focuses on education and women's rights\n\n2. Thomas Suarez - \"A 12-year-old app developer\"\n- Discusses his experience creating mobile apps as a young student\n- Inspirational technology talk\n\n3. Logan LaPlante - \"Hackschooling makes me happy\"\n- Talks about alternative education approaches\n- Delivered when he was 13\n\n4. Jack Andraka - \"A teen's breakthrough\"\n- Discusses developing a pancreatic cancer test as a high school student\n- Highlights youth innovation in medical research\n\n5. Shree Bose - \"A young scientist's breakthrough\"\n- Discusses her cancer research at a very young age\n- Won the Google Global Science Fair\n\n6. Zuriel Oduwole - \"Making a difference through education\"\n- Youngest person to direct a documentary\n- Advocates for girls' education\n\n7. Kid President (Robby Novak) - Various motivational talks\n- Humorous and inspirational presentations\n- Encourages kindness and positive thinking\n\nThese talks showcase youth creativity, innovation, and potential across various fields.",
